Update build dependencies
```
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y build-essential
```

Monitor gpu usage
```
watch -n 2 nvidia-smi
```

Monitor cpu/ram
```
htop
```

copy and paste a file
```
# copy a file
cp /path/to/dir/example.txt /target_path/

# copy a folder
cp -r /path/to/dir/myfolder /target_path/
```

Move a file or a folder
```
mv project_files /home/user/documents/
mv -i source_folder destination_folder #ask to confirm overwrite
mv -n source_folder destination_folder #Auto skip overwriting files with the same name
mv -v source_folder destination_folder #print out files being transferred
mv folder1 folder2 folder3 /home/user/backup/ #move multiple folders
```


See mounted drives
```
lsblk

lsblk -h # See filesystem type

df -h # Shows all mounted filesystems alongside their total storage capacity, used space, and available space in human-readable formats (GB/MB).
```
